<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="SQ2" checkit-title="Sequence properties and limits">
    <statement>
        <p>
            For each of the following sequences, determine which of the properties: <em>monotonic</em>, <em>bounded</em> and <em>convergent</em>, the sequence satisfies.  If a sequence is convergent, determine to what it converges.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <m>\displaystyle \left\{ \frac{5 \, \left(-1\right)^{n} n^{3}}{n^{2} + 1} \right\}_{n=0}^\infty</m>.
            </li>            
            <li>
                <m>\displaystyle \left\{ 3 \, \left(\frac{4}{7}\right)^{n} \right\}_{n=0}^\infty</m>.
            </li>            
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
       <ol>
            <li>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        The sequence is not monotonic.                
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The sequence is not bounded.                
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The sequence does not converge.                
                    </li>
                </ol>
                
            </li>            
            <li>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        The sequence is monotonic.                
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The sequence is bounded.                
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The sequence converges to <m>0</m>.                
                    </li>
                </ol>
                
            </li>            
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
